>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   AOE group question</span><hr size=1> Hi,<br>
I am just dying to really utilize my new spell scintillation.  Can anyone give me a couple of hints on how to get a AOE group together?  Where to look, who to ask, and what not.  And any tips on things to do/not do in the group would be appreciated as well.<br>
<br>
Best use I've had for scintillation so far is dueling a shaman.  His pet was on me, mine was on him.  I guess he snared my pet pretty well because suddenly he was on me too with my pet off in the distance just staring at us.  2 burst of scintillation and his pet was dead, he was bad hurt, and my pet was finally catching up to us.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 413<br> <font color=#333333>(3/6/03 11:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1878.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AOE group question</span><hr size=1> AoEing is dead. All the really good places to do it have been nerfed, in many cases repeatedly.<br>
<br>
Even if you do it there's no reason for a mage to be in an aoe without the prenerf rods over a wizard, since wizard aoes are so much more effective. <p>------------<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=433620">Kranken</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Convoker<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Xev<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->&quot;Where's my pet..?&quot;</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A> at: 3/6/03 11:57:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1852<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/03 5:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1878.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AOE group question</span><hr size=1> We don't talk as much about AoE groups anymore because it is nearly impossible to kill blues in PoP with AoE groups. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I do miss them though.<br>
<br>
Set-up can be debated, but normally something like this-<br>
1 healer<br>
1 enchanter<br>
1 puller<br>
3 AoE casters, wizards and magician preferred.  Wizards have better range of AE, but magicians have pets to clean up the last few mobs while the OoM wizards is sitting in the corner.<br>
<br>
Enchanter loads 3 different AE stuns, casters load AE nukes (which means scintillation for us).  Puller should be a hybrid class, and Bards are preferred.  They have AE slow, AE DoTs, and of course heal/mana songs for group.  Paladins make good pullers also, they can DA pull and do group heals.<br>
<br>
Some groups will go heavy on the nukers and eliminate either the healer or puller.  Such as having the cleric pull and do both jobs.  Or a shaman pull who can also AE slow.  Or add a 2nd enchanter for more stun power.  If you have paladin to help heal (&amp; rez if needed) with 2 enchanters stunning, there is a good chance you won't need a healer.  Or have a wizard go pull, it's up to you.<br>
<br>
It's a lot of fun when done right.  When everyone was capped at 60, it was pretty good xp in places like FG, Seb, and other decent zones with lots of blues.  I think my best hit was 16 mobs with 1 cast.  And if you have SCF-3, you can crit for 1200 dmg. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
